---
description: ESLint standards for TypeScript and TSX
globs: **/*.{ts,tsx}
alwaysApply: false
---

When writing or editing `*.ts` or `*.tsx`, follow `eslint.config.ts` and fix all lint/format issues before finishing.

### TypeScript
- Do not use `any` (`@typescript-eslint/no-explicit-any`).
- Do not add `eslint-disable` for lint rules without a brief justification.

### React (TSX)
- Destructure props in the function parameter list.
- Follow Rules of Hooks (`eslint-plugin-react-hooks`).
- Respect `react-refresh/only-export-components` where applicable.

### Before you finish
- Run ESLint on touched files and resolve errors (and warnings you introduced).